00:01:52,297 --> 00:01:58,097
"The Meiji Restoration Mystery Tour: Investigation Chapter"

9
00:01:58,797 --> 00:02:01,797
This Shrine here, is dedicated to Yoshida Shouin.

10
00:02:01,797 --> 00:02:04,697
The man who trained people who went on to become

11
00:02:04,697 --> 00:02:08,497
the leaders of the Meiji Restoration of Japan.

12
00:02:08,497 --> 00:02:09,597
Shouin?

13
00:02:09,597 --> 00:02:13,097
He lived 150 years ago.

14
00:02:13,097 --> 00:02:14,897
Meiji Regulation?

15
00:02:14,897 --> 00:02:18,297
Not regulation! Restoration!

16
00:02:18,297 --> 00:02:23,297
Shouin traveled throughout Japan to broaden his knowledge.

17
00:02:23,297 --> 00:02:24,597
And because he wanted to change the country,

18
00:02:24,597 --> 00:02:27,197
he also studied foreign systems as well.

19
00:02:27,197 --> 00:02:29,197
That was when Japan kept out foreign cultures.

20
00:02:29,197 --> 00:02:32,597
He studied Western culture, and, at the risk of his life,

21
00:02:32,597 --> 00:02:35,597
he even tried to stow away to America.

22
00:02:35,597 --> 00:02:39,097
But before his wish came true,

23
00:02:39,097 --> 00:02:41,597
Shouin was executed.

24
00:02:41,597 --> 00:02:45,797
Even so, others adopted Shouin's ambitions.

25
00:02:45,797 --> 00:02:47,497
And his pupils who listened to his teachings

26
00:02:47,497 --> 00:02:50,297
and went on to change society!

27
00:02:50,297 --> 00:02:51,597
Did you guys get that?

28
00:02:53,297 --> 00:02:56,297
Hey, why do all these kids have to come with us

29
00:02:56,297 --> 00:02:58,597
for our Japanese history assignment?

30
00:02:58,597 --> 00:03:00,297
Come on, it's okay.

31
00:03:00,297 --> 00:03:03,497
This is going to be a really fun day.

32
00:03:03,497 --> 00:03:05,997
That should be my line.

33
00:03:07,497 --> 00:03:08,497
What's going on?

34
00:03:08,497 --> 00:03:10,297
Give me that!

35
00:03:10,297 --> 00:03:11,697
No! Stop!

36
00:03:12,797 --> 00:03:13,797
No!

37
00:03:14,797 --> 00:03:16,297
Hey you!

38
00:03:16,297 --> 00:03:18,097
What are you doing?

39
00:03:19,397 --> 00:03:20,697
Wait up!

40
00:03:23,097 --> 00:03:24,397
Are you okay?

41
00:03:36,597 --> 00:03:38,397
You were threatened?

42
00:03:38,397 --> 00:03:39,397
Yes.

43
00:03:39,397 --> 00:03:41,297
They said, if I don't hand over this diary,

44
00:03:41,297 --> 00:03:42,797
they will harm me.

45
00:03:42,797 --> 00:03:45,397
And if I tell the police, they said I'd be jeopardizing my life.

46
00:03:45,397 --> 00:03:48,097
They told me that several times over the phone.

47
00:03:48,097 --> 00:03:50,197
Do you have an idea who it was?

48
00:03:50,197 --> 00:03:52,597
No, I have no idea.

49
00:03:52,597 --> 00:03:56,097
It looks like a very old diary.

50
00:03:56,097 --> 00:03:59,297
This is a gift from my grandfather.

51
00:03:59,297 --> 00:04:03,097
But there are only riddles and puzzles inside.

52
00:04:03,097 --> 00:04:04,297
Puzzles?

53
00:04:04,297 --> 00:04:06,697
My grandfather loved word games.

54
00:04:06,697 --> 00:04:09,697
And he would write down those in this book.

55
00:04:11,297 --> 00:04:14,197
But before I could get all the answers to the puzzles,

56
00:04:14,197 --> 00:04:18,997
my grandfather died five years ago on this day.

57
00:04:20,097 --> 00:04:23,397
My grandfather loved Shouin,

58
00:04:23,397 --> 00:04:27,197
that's why I went to the Shrine today.

59
00:04:27,197 --> 00:04:32,197
But why would they want an old diary?

60
00:04:32,197 --> 00:04:34,697
I do not know either.

61
00:04:34,697 --> 00:04:38,097
Mr. Mouri, could you please investigate this for me?

62
00:04:38,097 --> 00:04:40,897
Of course, I'll get right to it!

63
00:04:40,897 --> 00:04:42,097
What's that?

64
00:04:42,097 --> 00:04:44,997
That place that was torn off earlier,

65
00:04:44,997 --> 00:04:46,697
there's something in it.

66
00:04:46,697 --> 00:04:48,097
What is it?

67
00:04:48,097 --> 00:04:50,397
It says, "On November 30th,"

68
00:04:50,397 --> 00:04:53,997
"the treasure will be revealed in the sunset."

69
00:04:53,997 --> 00:04:56,597
"Solve the puzzle of the fox"

70
00:04:56,597 --> 00:04:58,197
Treasure?

71
00:04:58,197 --> 00:05:01,897
Ms. Kimiko, do you know anything about this?

72
00:05:01,897 --> 00:05:04,397
Treasure... I remember him saying...

73
00:05:04,397 --> 00:05:08,497
Kimiko, I have a magnificent treasure

74
00:05:08,497 --> 00:05:11,797
that could buy the whole country.

75
00:05:11,797 --> 00:05:13,997
Wha... what?

76
00:05:13,997 --> 00:05:16,797
Treasure that could buy the country?

77
00:05:16,797 --> 00:05:19,297
So, how many Unagi-bowls can I buy with that?

78
00:05:19,297 --> 00:05:22,497
Why does everything have to be measured with food?

79
00:05:22,497 --> 00:05:25,197
But, what is this fox puzzle?

80
00:05:25,197 --> 00:05:27,297
Look at this.

81
00:05:28,097 --> 00:05:30,497
There's a picture of a fox here in this page.

82
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:33,297
"Feed the carps to the fox",

83
00:05:33,297 --> 00:05:35,297
what does that mean?

84
00:05:35,297 --> 00:05:36,897
Carps in the moat...

85
00:05:36,897 --> 00:05:40,197
maybe it's about my hometown.

86
00:05:40,197 --> 00:05:42,397
Where is that?

87
00:05:42,397 --> 00:05:45,097
It's Tsuwano City of the Shimane prefecture.

88
00:05:45,097 --> 00:05:47,097
We have to go there at once!

89
00:05:47,097 --> 00:05:48,097
Why?

90
00:05:48,097 --> 00:05:51,197
Tomorrow is November 30th!

91
00:05:51,197 --> 00:05:55,497
We cannot let this chance pass us! We leave tomorrow morning!

92
00:05:55,497 --> 00:05:59,397
But how are we supposed to get tickets now?

93
00:05:59,397 --> 00:06:01,297
Leave that to me!

94
00:06:01,297 --> 00:06:04,297
Sonoko Suzuki is here to help!

95
00:06:04,297 --> 00:06:05,597
I'll use my family's connections,

96
00:06:05,597 --> 00:06:08,397
and whether it's a bullet train or express,

97
00:06:08,397 --> 00:06:10,497
I can get any ticket you need!

98
00:06:10,497 --> 00:06:13,197
That's the power of the daughter of the powerful Suzuki Family.

99
00:06:13,197 --> 00:06:14,197
Yes.

100
00:06:14,197 --> 00:06:17,397
And with this case in the hands of me, Kogorou Mouri,

101
00:06:17,397 --> 00:06:20,497
finding that treasure will be a piece of cake!

102
00:06:23,497 --> 00:06:25,497
We've got trouble.

103
00:06:25,497 --> 00:06:28,797
That woman has gone to see Detective Kogoro Mouri.

104
00:06:28,797 --> 00:06:32,297
I see, continue to monitor her moves.

105
00:06:40,897 --> 00:06:44,897
Thank you for accepting this case.

106
00:06:44,897 --> 00:06:47,097
No need to thank me!

107
00:06:47,097 --> 00:06:49,897
What does it mean?

108
00:06:49,897 --> 00:06:52,297
"Feed the carps to the fox".

109
00:06:52,297 --> 00:06:54,797
Do you think carp are tasty?

110
00:06:54,797 --> 00:06:56,897
Why do you guys have to tag along, too?

111
00:06:56,897 --> 00:06:58,397
Well, we think that's as plain as the nose on your face.

112
00:06:58,397 --> 00:07:02,097
We're the ones who saved Ms. Kimiko in the first place!

113
00:07:02,097 --> 00:07:03,597
Jeez...

114
00:07:03,597 --> 00:07:05,697
Writing down puzzles in a diary.

115
00:07:05,697 --> 00:07:08,797
Your grandfather must have been very creative.

116
00:07:08,797 --> 00:07:12,897
Yes, he was always thinking about interesting things.

117
00:07:14,497 --> 00:07:17,097
Kimiko, how many stamps

118
00:07:17,097 --> 00:07:21,597
do you need to send a letter to the future?

119
00:07:21,597 --> 00:07:23,297
Letter to the future?

120
00:07:23,297 --> 00:07:26,097
What is the answer?

121
00:07:27,297 --> 00:07:29,397
He never told me.

122
00:07:35,597 --> 00:07:39,297
Shin-Yamaguchi Station!

123
00:07:40,397 --> 00:07:44,397
From here we will take the Yamaguchi Line to get to Tsuwano.

124
00:07:44,397 --> 00:07:46,397
Kimiko!

125
00:07:46,397 --> 00:07:48,197
Kimiko, are you okay?

126
00:07:48,197 --> 00:07:49,697
Yes... Yes, I am.

127
00:07:49,697 --> 00:07:51,697
Kimiko, who is this?

128
00:07:51,697 --> 00:07:54,497
I'm Shigeru Kawaguchi, Kimiko's friend!

129
00:07:54,497 --> 00:07:57,797
I heard about what happened in Tokyo.

130
00:07:57,797 --> 00:08:00,797
We were the ones who save her, you know!

131
00:08:01,897 --> 00:08:03,897
And we are...

132
00:08:03,897 --> 00:08:05,697
The Youth Detective Squad!

133
00:08:07,397 --> 00:08:09,397
Good for you, guys.

134
00:08:09,397 --> 00:08:11,697
I owe you for protecting my friend.

135
00:08:11,697 --> 00:08:15,397
So, Kimiko, you're going back to Tsuwano, right?

136
00:08:15,397 --> 00:08:17,297
Yes... I am...

137
00:08:20,197 --> 00:08:22,597
Ms. Kimiko?

138
00:08:22,597 --> 00:08:26,097
Hey, it's me! Nine tickets were enough!

139
00:08:26,097 --> 00:08:28,497
Cancel the rest.

140
00:08:33,697 --> 00:08:34,997
Wow!

141
00:08:34,997 --> 00:08:37,297
I can feel the heat!

142
00:08:37,297 --> 00:08:39,297
The smell of it is amazing!

143
00:08:39,297 --> 00:08:41,797
All of you! Get on board this instant!

144
00:08:41,797 --> 00:08:43,097
Okay!

145
00:08:44,697 --> 00:08:48,397
"Shin-Yamaguchi to Tsuwano"

146
00:08:52,397 --> 00:08:53,597
For a limited time period,

147
00:08:53,597 --> 00:08:55,397
real steam locomotives service the Yamaguchi Line.

148
00:08:55,397 --> 00:08:57,697
It seems like there are no seats left.

149
00:08:57,697 --> 00:09:00,997
How did you get these tickets?

150
00:09:00,997 --> 00:09:04,797
I have some connections. It's pretty easy.

151
00:09:04,797 --> 00:09:06,497
Is there any hot spring spot?

152
00:09:06,497 --> 00:09:09,397
Around here, the Yuda hot springs are famous.

153
00:09:09,397 --> 00:09:13,697
That guy, Shigeru Kawaguchi isn't his real name.

154
00:09:13,697 --> 00:09:14,997
So you noticed?

155
00:09:14,997 --> 00:09:19,397
Kimiko's cell phone strap and his pendant are the same.

156
00:09:19,397 --> 00:09:20,997
There are initials engraved in the back of each one.

157
00:09:20,997 --> 00:09:24,797
Kimiko's is "K.K" for Kimiko Kobayakawa.

158
00:09:24,797 --> 00:09:26,397
But his says "A.T."

159
00:09:26,397 --> 00:09:27,697
If his name is Shiegeru Kawaguchi,

160
00:09:27,697 --> 00:09:29,697
it should be "S.K." right?

161
00:09:29,697 --> 00:09:32,697
I wonder why he is hiding his real name.

162
00:09:33,697 --> 00:09:37,397
I have some connections. It's pretty easy.

163
00:09:37,397 --> 00:09:38,597
I'll use my family's connections,

164
00:09:38,597 --> 00:09:41,597
and whether it's a bullet train or express,

165
00:09:41,597 --> 00:09:44,097
I can get any ticket you need!

166
00:09:44,097 --> 00:09:45,797
That means he might be connected

167
00:09:45,797 --> 00:09:48,197
to someone powerful in this area.

168
00:10:01,697 --> 00:10:03,397
What are you trying to do?

169
00:10:03,397 --> 00:10:05,697
Listen to me!

170
00:10:06,497 --> 00:10:07,897
What's the matter?

171
00:10:07,897 --> 00:10:10,197
Oh, I was looking for the bathroom.

172
00:10:10,197 --> 00:10:12,397
Oh, it's that way.

173
00:10:12,397 --> 00:10:14,097
Thanks!

174
00:10:19,297 --> 00:10:22,797
Tsuwano!

175
00:10:23,697 --> 00:10:25,797
Excuse me, are you Mr. Mouri?

176
00:10:25,797 --> 00:10:27,397
Yes, that is me.

177
00:10:27,397 --> 00:10:29,897
Thank you for coming from so far.

178
00:10:29,897 --> 00:10:33,797
My name is Tsuneo Kikkawa. I work for the Kobayakawa family.

179
00:10:33,797 --> 00:10:36,097
Thank you for waiting on us.

180
00:10:36,097 --> 00:10:38,497
Where is Ms. Kimiko?

181
00:10:38,497 --> 00:10:40,797
She was with us just now.

182
00:10:40,797 --> 00:10:42,897
Maybe she got kidnapped?

183
00:10:42,897 --> 00:10:44,597
I'm here!

184
00:10:44,597 --> 00:10:46,897
I forgot to get a gift for my mother.

185
00:10:46,897 --> 00:10:48,497
I just ran to get something.

186
00:10:48,497 --> 00:10:49,597
That's a relief!

187
00:10:49,597 --> 00:10:50,797
It's funny that

188
00:10:50,797 --> 00:10:53,497
I was just in Tokyo, but I'm buying her a gift here.

189
00:10:55,397 --> 00:10:57,297
Where did your friend go?

190
00:10:57,297 --> 00:10:59,797
He left already.

191
00:10:59,797 --> 00:11:01,197
Come on, let's go.

192
00:11:04,997 --> 00:11:08,697
Development is our town's future!

193
00:11:08,697 --> 00:11:11,197
And I believe everyone knows what I've done for the community.

194
00:11:11,197 --> 00:11:12,397
Who is that?

195
00:11:13,797 --> 00:11:15,797
His name is Hisamichi Takahashi.

196
00:11:15,797 --> 00:11:18,097
He is involved in real estate and construction

197
00:11:18,097 --> 00:11:19,297
around this area.

198
00:11:19,297 --> 00:11:20,597
He has extensive business operations,

199
00:11:20,597 --> 00:11:23,197
developing resorts and such.

200
00:11:23,197 --> 00:11:24,897
Now he's announcing his candidacy

201
00:11:24,897 --> 00:11:27,097
as a member of the prefectural assembly.

202
00:11:27,097 --> 00:11:32,197
And this area will be vitalized and life will be better for everyone.

203
00:11:32,197 --> 00:11:34,897
And the one who can do it is me, Hisamichi Takahashi!

204
00:11:34,897 --> 00:11:37,297
And only me, Hisamichi Takahashi!

205
00:11:37,297 --> 00:11:39,397
Mr. Takahashi makes me feel safe and secure.

206
00:11:39,397 --> 00:11:42,597
Yes, he's the one who loves this town the most.

207
00:11:42,597 --> 00:11:46,097
To think such a splendid father could have a son like that is too bad...

208
00:11:46,097 --> 00:11:48,197
Atsushi, right?

209
00:11:48,197 --> 00:11:51,797
How long is he going to keep acting like a punk?

210
00:11:53,097 --> 00:11:55,897
This is Tonomachi Street.

211
00:11:55,897 --> 00:11:59,797
And this is where the ancient samurai houses are still standing.

212
00:11:59,797 --> 00:12:01,897
Wow, look at the size of that carp!

213
00:12:01,897 --> 00:12:07,097
In the old days, they were raised as emergency food.

214
00:12:07,097 --> 00:12:10,597
Are we going to feed all the carp to the fox?

215
00:12:10,597 --> 00:12:13,597
What are you talking about? This is a puzzle, remember?

216
00:12:13,597 --> 00:12:16,197
We're not actually gonna feed them!

217
00:12:16,197 --> 00:12:17,497
I know that bit!

218
00:12:19,297 --> 00:12:21,297
Thank you so much.

219
00:12:21,297 --> 00:12:24,997
No need to. I am glad that your daughter is back safe.

220
00:12:24,997 --> 00:12:29,797
Our house was recently robbed too.

221
00:12:29,797 --> 00:12:30,797
What?

222
00:12:30,797 --> 00:12:33,997
Maybe they were looking for the diary?

223
00:12:33,997 --> 00:12:35,597
Maybe so.

224
00:12:36,597 --> 00:12:41,197
Mr. Mouri, please catch the people who are doing this.

225
00:12:41,197 --> 00:12:43,197
Of course.

226
00:12:43,197 --> 00:12:45,697
So, it seems that Ms. Kimiko has heard

227
00:12:45,697 --> 00:12:47,897
about this treasure from her grandfather.

228
00:12:47,897 --> 00:12:49,297
Have you heard of this before?

229
00:12:49,297 --> 00:12:53,097
Yes, I have heard about it.

230
00:12:53,097 --> 00:12:55,297
I heard that, because of this treasure,

231
00:12:55,297 --> 00:12:59,397
the Kobayakawa family was restored after the War.

232
00:12:59,397 --> 00:13:05,397
But I know that it wasn't only because of this treasure.

233
00:13:05,397 --> 00:13:08,097
It was by my father's hard work that made it happen.

234
00:13:08,097 --> 00:13:12,097
But there are some who don't think so.

235
00:13:12,097 --> 00:13:14,697
Especially some people who rose to power in the turmoil

236
00:13:14,697 --> 00:13:16,497
after the Second World War.

237
00:13:16,497 --> 00:13:20,697
Since we've been deeply trusted by the local people historically,

238
00:13:20,697 --> 00:13:23,597
they take advantage of every opportunity to get at the Kobayakawa family.

239
00:13:23,597 --> 00:13:28,997
I see, so they might be the ones after the diary.

240
00:13:28,997 --> 00:13:33,097
-We have to find the treasure before they do. -Yes.

241
00:13:33,097 --> 00:13:36,197
Can I eat now?

242
00:13:36,197 --> 00:13:38,197
Oh, I'm so sorry!

243
00:13:38,197 --> 00:13:39,897
Please go ahead!

244
00:13:39,897 --> 00:13:41,497
Thank you!

245
00:13:41,497 --> 00:13:43,897
It is the sweets from Yamaguchi Prefecture.

246
00:13:43,897 --> 00:13:47,697
It is slightly different from the ones in Nagoya.

247
00:13:50,497 --> 00:13:52,697
-It's so good! -It's like jelly!

248
00:13:52,697 --> 00:13:54,897
Mine already gone!

249
00:13:58,297 --> 00:14:03,697
To feed the fox the carp means the carp disappear.

250
00:14:03,697 --> 00:14:04,797
Mitsuhiko,

251
00:14:04,797 --> 00:14:06,597
can you hand me the copy of this picture?

252
00:14:06,597 --> 00:14:08,597
Yeah, sure.

253
00:14:11,697 --> 00:14:13,997
-Conan? -What's going on?

254
00:14:15,597 --> 00:14:16,797
How about this way?

255
00:14:18,397 --> 00:14:20,897
The carp disappeared!

256
00:14:21,797 --> 00:14:23,697
-It's true. -Oh, my...

257
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:28,097
"Feed the carp" should be about this!

258
00:14:28,097 --> 00:14:32,297
Well, you just folded it.

259
00:14:32,297 --> 00:14:34,097
But look, there are letters.

260
00:14:34,097 --> 00:14:35,197
What?

261
00:14:35,197 --> 00:14:38,997
The patterns come together and form letters!

262
00:14:38,997 --> 00:14:42,597
"Below the top of the hidden Inari"?

263
00:14:42,597 --> 00:14:44,297
Inari.

264
00:14:44,297 --> 00:14:46,997
I can only think of the Taikodani Inari Shrine in this area.

265
00:14:46,997 --> 00:14:50,697
That's it! The treasure is at the Taikodani Inari Shrine!

266
00:14:50,697 --> 00:14:52,897
All right, let's go!

267
00:14:59,975 --> 00:15:03,975
This is... an amazing numbers of arches...

