A thousand?

270
00:15:08,975 --> 00:15:11,675
Are we going to walk up there?

271
00:15:11,675 --> 00:15:13,675
We have no choice.

272
00:15:18,375 --> 00:15:20,375
I can't do it!

273
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:23,175
Come on, Genta!

274
00:15:23,175 --> 00:15:25,375
Just a little more!

275
00:15:33,475 --> 00:15:34,775
We made it!

276
00:15:35,575 --> 00:15:38,775
-It's pretty. -Look at the view!

277
00:15:38,775 --> 00:15:44,375
So what does " Below the top of the hidden Inari" mean?

278
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:45,775
Hey, what's that?

279
00:15:45,775 --> 00:15:49,375
-Is it food? -Fried tofu?

280
00:15:49,375 --> 00:15:52,475
That is not for eating. It's an offering.

281
00:15:52,475 --> 00:15:55,575
Because fried tofu is the fox's favorite food.

282
00:15:55,575 --> 00:15:58,175
Where do they put them?

283
00:15:58,175 --> 00:15:59,975
Are you planning to steal them?

284
00:15:59,975 --> 00:16:01,875
You'll get punished!

285
00:16:01,875 --> 00:16:04,875
I'm just asking!

286
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:07,775
They either put it at the main building,

287
00:16:07,775 --> 00:16:10,675
or in the shrine at the back.

288
00:16:10,675 --> 00:16:14,575
Maybe that's the hidden Inari?

289
00:16:18,675 --> 00:16:20,475
Here?

290
00:16:20,475 --> 00:16:23,275
I don't see anything.

291
00:16:23,275 --> 00:16:25,675
I found the fried tofu!

292
00:16:25,675 --> 00:16:28,175
Now you know you can't get them.

293
00:16:28,175 --> 00:16:31,675
-I said I'm not! -This is awesome.

294
00:16:31,675 --> 00:16:33,875
Hey guys, look at this!

295
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:36,975
So many foxes in there!

296
00:16:36,975 --> 00:16:38,275
You're right.

297
00:16:38,275 --> 00:16:40,275
It's cool.

298
00:16:40,275 --> 00:16:44,475
I know! The hidden Inari is around here!

299
00:16:44,475 --> 00:16:47,075
No, not there, it's here.

300
00:16:50,475 --> 00:16:53,675
This is the hidden Inari.

301
00:16:53,675 --> 00:16:56,875
Now, "Below the top of the hidden Inari"

302
00:16:56,875 --> 00:17:00,175
There is a fried tofu figure made of stone.

303
00:17:00,175 --> 00:17:01,975
Fried tofu?

304
00:17:01,975 --> 00:17:04,675
I got it! The kanji that means "Top"

305
00:17:04,675 --> 00:17:06,575
also could translate to the meaning of fried tofu.

306
00:17:06,575 --> 00:17:10,875
So the treasure should be under the fried tofu made of stone!

307
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:14,975
-Awesome, Mitsuhiko! -You are a genius!

308
00:17:14,975 --> 00:17:17,075
Thanks, guys!

309
00:17:19,275 --> 00:17:20,575
A jar?

310
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:23,275
What's in there?

311
00:17:23,275 --> 00:17:27,275
Well, there is some kind of paper.

312
00:17:27,275 --> 00:17:29,275
This is...

313
00:17:29,275 --> 00:17:30,975
It looks like a map.

314
00:17:30,975 --> 00:17:33,375
There's something written on the top!

315
00:17:33,375 --> 00:17:35,075
What does it say?

316
00:17:35,075 --> 00:17:37,075
"Reflect the castle in the eye of the cat"

317
00:17:37,075 --> 00:17:39,575
"and look under the mouse."

318
00:17:39,575 --> 00:17:41,175
What does that mean?

319
00:17:41,175 --> 00:17:43,075
A cat...

320
00:17:43,675 --> 00:17:46,375
It should be about this.

321
00:17:46,375 --> 00:17:48,875
I see holes in it.

322
00:17:48,875 --> 00:17:52,275
Not a mouse in any of the pages.

323
00:17:52,275 --> 00:17:54,675
Another puzzle, huh?

324
00:17:54,675 --> 00:17:59,775
This seems like the old map of the city of Hagi.

325
00:17:59,775 --> 00:18:02,775
Hagi is in Yamaguchi Prefecture.

326
00:18:02,775 --> 00:18:07,675
Yes, the city is linked to Shouin whom my grandfather adored.

327
00:18:07,675 --> 00:18:11,975
I see, so the treasure should be in Hagi.

328
00:18:12,775 --> 00:18:16,075
I see. They are headed for Hagi.

329
00:18:16,075 --> 00:18:19,475
Stay with them, you hear me?

330
00:18:23,875 --> 00:18:26,075
Where is Kimiko?

331
00:18:27,175 --> 00:18:29,575
I'm coming!

332
00:18:38,875 --> 00:18:41,275
It feels like a very old town.

333
00:18:41,275 --> 00:18:44,775
They have preserved the town as it is was like in the old days.

334
00:18:44,775 --> 00:18:47,575
So you can even walk through the town

335
00:18:47,575 --> 00:18:50,075
even if you had a map from the Edo Period!

336
00:18:50,075 --> 00:18:51,675
That is marvelous!

337
00:18:51,675 --> 00:18:54,275
The many people who were involved in the Meiji Restoration

338
00:18:54,275 --> 00:18:56,575
have also seen this same view today.

339
00:18:56,575 --> 00:18:59,875
That's right! This is where the Meiji Restoration all began!

340
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:02,275
Here we go. The Meiji Reservation.

341
00:19:02,275 --> 00:19:04,475
Restoration!

342
00:19:04,475 --> 00:19:07,275
That's the reform that gave Japan its chance

343
00:19:07,275 --> 00:19:09,575
to become a modern country like it is today.

344
00:19:09,575 --> 00:19:12,475
Many people who were involved in the Meiji Restoration

345
00:19:12,475 --> 00:19:14,475
were from Hagi.

346
00:19:14,475 --> 00:19:15,875
I see!

347
00:19:15,875 --> 00:19:18,375
"Hagi Museum East Entrance"

348
00:19:20,175 --> 00:19:21,975
The Cat Street?

349
00:19:22,675 --> 00:19:24,775
Does this have anything to do with that code?

350
00:19:24,775 --> 00:19:30,575
About 250 streets are named like that.

351
00:19:30,575 --> 00:19:33,875
This street is named after a person who was close to Terumoto Mouri,

352
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:36,975
and since he was fond of cats,

353
00:19:36,975 --> 00:19:39,275
they called it the Cat Street.

354
00:19:40,475 --> 00:19:42,475
Look! A real cat!

355
00:19:42,475 --> 00:19:47,175
Oh, kitty cat! I know, I got it!

356
00:19:47,175 --> 00:19:49,575
You mean you solved the puzzle?

357
00:19:49,575 --> 00:19:50,675
Yes!

358
00:19:50,675 --> 00:19:53,975
They meant the white walls, not the castle!

359
00:19:53,975 --> 00:19:57,175
That means that one of these cats is watching a wall

360
00:19:57,175 --> 00:20:01,175
which will point out where the treasure is!

361
00:20:01,175 --> 00:20:04,475
And that cat right there is looking at it right...

362
00:20:04,475 --> 00:20:06,675
Wait! Please wait, Kitty!

363
00:20:06,675 --> 00:20:09,575
I'm very sure that he is wrong.

364
00:20:09,575 --> 00:20:12,875
Mr. Mouri sure has a sense of humor.

365
00:20:12,875 --> 00:20:15,575
The problem is that he's dead serious.

366
00:20:20,375 --> 00:20:23,775
That was the guy who called himself Shigeru Kawaguchi?

367
00:20:28,675 --> 00:20:30,875
Can't you understand what I'm saying?

368
00:20:30,875 --> 00:20:32,875
But...

369
00:20:32,875 --> 00:20:35,175
It is him.

370
00:20:36,375 --> 00:20:37,675
That man...

371
00:20:40,075 --> 00:20:42,475
The guy who attacked Kimiko!

372
00:20:44,075 --> 00:20:47,475
This is where the doctor in the Edo period named Shusuke Aoki

373
00:20:47,475 --> 00:20:49,075
was living.

374
00:20:49,075 --> 00:20:51,775
They say that they found treasure buried here.

375
00:20:51,775 --> 00:20:53,675
You know well!

376
00:20:53,675 --> 00:20:55,475
Really?

377
00:20:55,475 --> 00:20:58,975
Yes, they say that they found it from under the cellar.

378
00:20:58,975 --> 00:21:01,175
Treasure!

379
00:21:01,875 --> 00:21:03,675
There is a treasure, I'm sure!

380
00:21:03,675 --> 00:21:05,075
I think so too!

381
00:21:05,075 --> 00:21:06,475
I'm getting excited!

382
00:21:06,475 --> 00:21:09,275
Me too!

383
00:21:09,275 --> 00:21:12,175
Now, let's head to the Hagi Castle!

384
00:21:19,175 --> 00:21:23,675
What does Shigeru have to do with those men?

385
00:21:23,675 --> 00:21:26,075
And who is he exactly?

386
00:21:28,875 --> 00:21:31,375
-Hurry up! -Be quiet!

387
00:21:31,375 --> 00:21:34,775
Hey! What do you think you're doing?

388
00:21:34,775 --> 00:21:37,175
-The keys! -You little brat!

389
00:21:37,175 --> 00:21:39,675
Police! This way! Come quick!

390
00:21:39,675 --> 00:21:41,475
Hurry up! We're moving!

391
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:44,875
Mitsuhiko!

392
00:21:45,675 --> 00:21:47,175
What's going on?

393
00:21:47,175 --> 00:21:48,375
Thanks!

394
00:21:54,975 --> 00:21:56,375
You're not getting away!

395
00:22:03,575 --> 00:22:05,375
Crack!

396
00:22:05,375 --> 00:22:08,475
No, I didn't think they would go this far.

397
00:22:08,475 --> 00:22:12,075
I didn't pay enough attention.

398
00:22:12,075 --> 00:22:16,275
Is there really a treasure that could buy a country?

399
00:22:16,275 --> 00:22:21,675
And who are those men?

400
00:22:21,675 --> 00:22:23,175
And that voice...

401
00:22:23,175 --> 00:22:25,775
Police! This way! Come quick!

402
00:22:25,775 --> 00:22:28,175
I know that voice, and it is...

403
00:23:51,175 --> 00:23:53,075
We have the girl and the children.

404
00:23:53,075 --> 00:23:55,775
Find that treasure or else!

405
00:23:58,075 --> 00:23:59,175
Conan?

406
00:23:59,175 --> 00:24:00,375
Mitsuhiko?

407
00:24:01,075 --> 00:24:02,775
Mitsuhiko!

408
00:24:02,775 --> 00:24:05,875
"Draw the map in the cave where the water goblin lives."

409
00:24:05,875 --> 00:24:08,975
Where is this cave?

410
00:24:08,975 --> 00:24:11,475
We have to hurry.

411
00:24:11,475 --> 00:24:14,875
We only have time until sunset!

412
00:24:14,875 --> 00:24:16,475
Next Conan,

413
00:24:16,475 --> 00:24:20,375
"The Meiji Restoration Mystery Tour: Deciphering Chapter"

